OL,6,FWhen asked how such a prolific abuser
OL,7,Fcould hide in plain sight, Ms Pickles
OL,8,Fcommented: "They start by grooming the
OL,9,Fenvironment they're in, removing any
OL,10,Fobstacles. So for him, becoming a big
OL,11,Fnoise, being an important person,
OL,12,Fbeing an important leader within
OL,13,Funions, speaking to Welsh
OL,14,FGovernment...that all provided him
OL,15,Fwith the cover. So everyone felt
